caption: The last day of the Olympics and I attended the 8.30am Sunday morning service. A quiet service allowing for a moment of reflection and to give thanks and prayers for a spectacular two weeks and for all the athletes, volunteers and everyone else who has contributed to making them a success.

We arrived to an underwhelming building but a warm greeting. We stayed only to hear a wonderful choir, see a congregation of mixed heritages, races, and a beautiful sung liturgy well crafted to invite one into the holy. The sermon was superb. What was created in the space, became the sacred space.  The after service gathering was warm, mixed generational, inclusive. The day was set for a good beginning and we could not have asked for more. Thank you all.

I really enjoyed the service in this church. It is small,  but it was divine. The priest's sermon captured the audience and the choir was simply divine. It seems to have a strong sense of community. The absolute plus is that THEY SPEAK ENGLISH!!!!
As a Brit married to a French man it was nice to find a church service I could understand whilst visiting his family. The church was very welcoming, and the choir was fantastic!
God save the Queen. God bless you. Love Jesus for ever Advitam Eternam
Very beautiful Anglican church, with very understandable preaching. It's a marvelous and a magnificent church and have a nice day.

St George is an Anglo-Catholic church. She has a very good choir. The congregation is mixed, regarding ages, races, and sexual orientations. Only one regret: we don't have priestesses yet. I am sure that one day my prayers will be answered.
I think it is used together with the Pont Neuf Presbyterian Church. Champs-Elysées...located about 500 meters from the Arc de Triomphe.
I stopped by for the Christmas market Very nice!
To experience the spiritual energy of faith
